["Horns Creek is a 1.73\u00a0mi (2.78\u00a0km) long 2nd order tributary to the Fisher River in Surry County, North Carolina.","Horns Creek rises 0.5 miles south of Stotts Knob.  Horns Creek then flows southeast to join the Fisher River about 0.25 miles west of Turkey Ford, North Carolina.[2]","Horns Creek drains 1.08 square miles (2.8\u00a0km2) of area, receives about 48.1 in\/year of precipitation, has a wetness index of 301.57, and is about 66% forested.[4]","This article related to a river in North Carolina is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it."]